APS_Status_t status

Detailed Description

The structure is used to report the result of a binding request. Conforms to APSME-BIND.confirm primitive.

Definition at line 61 of file apsmeBind.h.

Field Documentation

APS_Status_t APS_BindConf_t::status

This parameter can take a value from the following list:

  • APS_SUCCESS_STATUS - the binding link has been successfully created,
  • APS_TABLE_FULL_STATUS - the binding table capacity has been exceeded,
  • APS_NOT_SUPPORTED_STATUS - the device does not support the binding table,
  • APS_ILLEGAL_REQUEST_STATUS - the device is not joined to a network, or one of the parameters has a value that is out of range.
